    "narrative": "For LawDog\u2019s April 13th slate, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (78.03) and **Bryson Stott** (72.63) anchor the lineup as our most reliable options. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** benefits from a soft matchup against Liberatore, where his power profile remains elite despite a slight park disadvantage. **Bryson Stott** is the day's primary riser, with his base projection surging nearly 20 points due to a generous 4.83 xERA from Assad and a favorable wind forecast that boosts his slugging potential. **Geraldo Perdomo** (72.48) also earns a strong start, with a massive +16% park adjustment making him a high-efficiency play in the MI slot despite his lower power ceiling.\n\nWe are prioritizing aggressive baserunning opportunities today, which keeps **Masyn Winn** (55.64) and **Jeremiah Jackson** (61.75) in the mix, even with some volatility in their batted-ball profiles. **Jeremiah Jackson** particularly benefits from the high-scoring environment against Nelson, elevating his score above the marginal threshold. The most difficult bench decision involved **Yainer Diaz** (40.13), who remains in the UTIL spot only by the thinnest of margins. While his 40.13 score is precarious, he avoided being benched simply because of the current roster constraints; had **Gleyber Torres** or **Jung Hoo Lee** been active and healthy today, **Yainer Diaz** would have been relegated to the pine to preserve our game caps against a tough arm in Kirby.\n\nRisk management is paramount today given the \"Lineup Pending\" status for **Will Smith**, whose score of 57.93 assumes he maintains the #3 hole. If he drops lower in the order, his utility diminishes rapidly. Furthermore, **Lawrence Butler** (60.62) faces a stiff test against Eovaldi (3.17 xERA); while his platoon edge and leadoff status keep him above the 60-point \"Strong\" threshold, he is our highest-risk start. We are monitoring these games closely, keeping **Jonathan Aranda**, **Wenceel Perez**, **Gavin Sheets**, and **Drew Gilbert** ready on the bench if the mid-game tactical shifts require defensive substitutions or late-inning stolen base specialists to close the gap in our 5x5 categories.",
